  "title": "DevOps Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Description:</strong></p><p>•Design, develop, and maintain efficient, scalable, and secure backend systems and APIs, Proficiency in backend programming language such as Java</p><p>•Design and implement robust CI/CD pipelines using tools such as Jenkins, JFrog Artifactory, and Bitbucket, ensuring automated builds, testing, and deployments.</p><p>•Perform OCP/PCF administration tasks, including deployment, scaling, and troubleshooting of containerized applications.</p><p>•Integrate and manage observability tools such as Grafana and Greylog to monitor system health, performance, and troubleshoot issues.</p><p>•Write clean, well-designed, and testable code, ensuring high quality and adherence to industry best practices.</p><p>•Collaborate effectively with cross-functional teams, including frontend developers, UI/UX designers, and product managers, to deliver integrated solutions.</p><p>•Work collaboratively with the infrastructure team to stand up and maintain critical environments including OpenShift Container Platform (OCP), Redis, PostgreSQL, S3, and NFS.</p><p>•Contribute to the setup and configuration of network routes, load balancing, firewalls.</p><p>•Manage SSL certificates, identity, and access management solutions.</p><p>•Experience with Cypher queries writing is a plus.</p><p></p>",
